Airbrite is an e-commerce software company that helps small businesses and crowdfunding graduates process orders. Founded in 2012, when it graduated from the incubator Y Combinator, it is backed by such venture capital investors as YC's financing arm, Ron Conway's SV Angel and others. The company is based in San Francisco, California.
Airbrite was founded by Chris Tsai, Brian Nguyen and Peter Shih. It works with such early-stage hardware companies as Pebble and Lockitron. The company is part of a wave of startups processing orders for mobile- and tablet-based commerce. It uses Javascript and Node.js as the basis for its Open API.
